The paper deals with the logical foundations of information theory, which is a subfield of computer science. The paper introduces a new logic of partitions and develops the concept of entropy based on this logic. This makes cs.IT the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with combinatorial aspects of partitions, which makes cs.LO and cs.DM likely sub-categories. The paper also uses concepts from graph theory and combinatorics, which makes cs.DS a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the inclusion-exclusion principle, which is a fundamental concept in combinatorics and discrete mathematics, making cs.CC a possible sub-category.
